  [Text] The brothers President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih,
chairman of the [Yemeni] Presidential Council, and Syrian
President Hafiz al-Asad held a closed meeting at the People's
Palace in Damascus this evening.
  The Yemeni News Agency, SABA' has learned that the talks
addressed the strong fraternal bilateral ties, the means of
promoting them, issues of common interest to the two fraternal
countries, and Arab issues.
  The brother Presidential Council chairman briefed his
brother
His Excellency President Hafiz al-Asad on developments in our
country in light of the accord document and the efforts made to
contain the crisis and ensure the convening of meetings by the
Constitutional institutions to help implement the accord
document.
  The session of Yemeni-Syrian talks was held at the People's
Palace at 1730, Damascus time, today. The talks were cochaired
by brothers Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman of
the Presidential Council, and His Excellency President Hafiz
al-Asad of the Syrian Arab Republic.
  During this session of talks, the two leaders reviewed
current Arab developments and issues of interest to our Arab
nation, foremost among which are developments in the Palestine
question and the efforts under way to achieve a just and
comprehensive peace in the region on the basis of regaining Arab
rights.
  The two leaders stressed the need to promote efforts to
clear
the Arab atmosphere and restore Arab solidarity so Arabs can
cope with the enormous challenges facing our Arab nation, and so
just, comprehensive, and durable peace can be achieved in the
region. Issues pertaining to the fraternal bilateral ties were
also addressed.
  His Excellency President Hafiz al-Asad of the Syrian Arab
Republic has reiterated Syria's support for our people, and for
our country's stability. He also emphasized that Syria supports
all efforts to safeguard Yemeni unity and enhance its march,
given that Yemeni unity is a significant pan-Arab accomplishment
along the path of Arab unity, and a gain that is dear to all
Arabs. He asserted that Yemen's security, stability, and safety
concern Syria and all the sons of the Arab nation, given that
the pan-Arab security is an indivisible whole.
  For his part, the brother president expressed his
appreciation of the fraternal efforts and stands of the
fraternal Syrians, as manifested in their support for the march
of unity and democracy in our country. He indicated that the
Yemeni-Syrian ties are fraternal and strong.
  At the outset of this session of talks, His Excellency
President Hafiz al-Asad welcomed the brother Presidential
Council chairman and the delegation accompanying him on this
visit. He noted the strong and deep fraternal ties binding the
two fraternal peoples. He expressed his confidence that this
visit will reinforce these strong ties in the interest of the
two fraternal peoples and the Arab nation.
  This session of talks was attended for Yemen by Deputy Prime
Minister 'Abd-al-Wahhab al-Anisi, Minister of Planning and
Development Dr. 'Abd-al-Karim al-Iryani, Foreign Affairs
Minister Muhammad Salim Basindwah, Presidential Council Office
Chief 'Ali Muhammad al-Anisi, and Yemeni Ambassador to Syria
Muhammad Shutfah. For Syria, the talks were attended by Vice
President 'Abd-al-Halim Khaddam, Prime Minister Mahmud al-Zu'bi,
Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar', and Minister of State for
Foreign Affairs Nasir Qaddur.

</TEXT>

