-- for your protection, you might say.;    The cookies (the name means lady's
kisses) look like miniature hamburger buns with a thin chocolate filling.
They're not cheap, but that's probably a good thing. Prices range from 40
cents to 75 cents for individual cookies and $8 to $10 for half-pound sacks.
Get them at the Gourmet Giraffe in Los Gatos, Caffe Classico in Campbell, The
Coffee Roasting Club in Morgan Hill and Gilroy, Continental Deli in Aptos and
La Villa, Villa Lanza and Marco's, all in San Jose.  </LEADPARA>
