  [Text] Lieutenant General brother 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih,
chairman of the Presidential Council, yesterday evening received
brother Dr. Khalid al-Karaki, His Majesty King Husayn's adviser.
  Al-Karaki arrived in Sanaa with a Jordanian military team,
led by Major Gen. 'Id Kamil, assistant to the Jordanian Army
chief of staff. The Jordanian team will be partly responsible
for carrying out the military aspect of the accord document
signed in the Jordanian capital. It will also handle part of
the the work of the military committee.
  Dr. al-Karaki conveyed a message from King Husayn to his
brother the chairman of the Presidential Council spelling out
his majesty's efforts to bridge viewpoints and implement the
accord document. The message reiterated Jordan's keenness to
see the accord document translated on the ground as an
achievement that concerns the Arab nation as well as the Yemeni
people. It indicated that it is the duty of all Arabs to rally
to Yemen's unity as a pan-Arab project embodying the aspirations
of Arab unionists and holding out the hope that the dawn of Arab
unity has arrived.
  President Salih and Dr. al-Karaki reviewed Yemeni
developments against the backdrop of the accord document. The
president told him he and the Yemeni people were appreciative of
His Majesty King Husayn's and the Jordanian people's pan-Arab
attitude and genuine concern for unity and democracy in our
country. The president said he appreciated that Jordan was
doing all it could to help Yemen ride out the tough challenges
left by the political crisis. President Salih noted that these
efforts were crowned by Amman hosting the gathering of Yemeni
political and social figures to witness the ceremonies for
signing the accord document. Our people, the president told Dr.
al-Karaki, will always recognize Jordan's brotherly stands that
dramatize the profundity of ties between the two brother peoples.
  The president asked him to convey his greetings to his
brother His Majesty King Husayn and best wishes for the
brotherly Jordanian people. The meeting was attended by brother
'Ali Muhammad al-Anisi, the head of the Presidential Office;
Maj. Gen. 'Id Kamil, assistant to the Jordanian Army chief of
staff; and Fayiz al-Rubayyi', the Jordanian ambassador to our
country.

