  [Text] In a pre-departure statement in Sanaa today, UN
envoy Lakhdar Brahimi expressed disappointment at the collapse
of yesterday's cease-fire agreement. He stressed that the
conflict can be solved through dialogue between the concerned
parties, but such a dialogue is still not possible as the south
wants a complete halt to battles and full northern commitment to
a cease-fire before anything else. As for the conditions of the
north, here is 'Abd-al-Salam al-'Ansi, chairman of the General
